# Environment variables the Cloud Run Job reads at runtime.
#
# These are set on the Job by scripts/bootstrap.sh (static ones) and overridden
# per-execution by scripts/handoff.sh (the session-specific ones). This file is
# documentation only — you don't need to edit it.

# --- set once on the Job (bootstrap) ---------------------------------------
# BUCKET               GCS bucket for transcripts / patches / logs.
# FIRESTORE_DATABASE   Firestore database id (usually "(default)").
# MAX_HOURS            Soft wall-clock guard; agent is killed just under this.
# CLAUDE_AUTH_MODE     subscription | apikey | vertex

# --- mounted secrets (bootstrap wires these; handoff pushes real values) ----
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN   Claude subscription OAuth token (env).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY         Anthropic API key (env).
# OPENAI_API_KEY            OpenAI API key (env).
# GIT_TOKEN                 GitHub token used to clone/push/open PRs (env).
# /secrets/codex/auth.json  Codex auth.json (file mount).
# (Placeholder values are treated as "unset" by the entrypoint.)

# --- set per-execution (handoff.sh --update-env-vars) -----------------------
# SESSION_ID     Unique id; drives the handoff/<id> branch + Firestore doc + GCS prefix.
# AGENT          claude | codex
# REPO_URL       https remote the job clones and pushes to.
# BASE_BRANCH    Branch the work is based on.
# TASK_B64       base64-encoded task/prompt text.
# RESUME         "1" on follow-up runs (skip patch apply, restore transcript, resume).
# OPEN_PR        "1" to open a PR after pushing (default), "0" to only push the branch.
